---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
        <head>
                <BaseHead title={`Start Here | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="An introduction to Jack Maguire, his philosophy, and his work." />
                <style>
                        main {
                                width: 720px;
                                max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
                                margin: auto;
                                padding: 3em 1em;
                        }
                        .prose h2 {
                                font-size: 1.8em;
                                margin-top: 2em;
                                margin-bottom: 0.5em;
                                color: rgb(var(--black));
                        }
                        .prose p {
                                margin-bottom: 1.5em;
                                line-height: 1.8;
                                color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
                        }
                        .prose strong {
                                color: rgb(var(--black));
                        }
                        .note {
                                padding: 1.5em;
                                background-color: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.2);
                                border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
                                margin: 2em 0;
                                font-style: italic;
                        }
                </style>
        </head>
        <body>
                <Header />
                <main>
                        <h1>Start Here</h1>
                        <div class="prose">
                                <p>Welcome to the index. This page maps my operating system and outlines the frameworks guiding my work, research, and personal life. My name is Jack Maguire, and I am based in the East Village of New York City. This archive serves as a repository for my writing and technical evaluations across performance marketing, urbanism, travel architecture, and gastronomy.</p>

                                <h2>The Engine of Performance Marketing</h2>

                                <p>My career as a Senior Paid Social Media Director at National Debt Relief focuses on scaling campaign structures across Meta, TikTok, and Snapchat. The advertising industry suffers from noise and a reliance on vanity metrics. My methodology requires deterministic attribution and incrementality. Managing high-volume restaurant operations early in my career instilled a deep understanding of systems thinking and human friction. In media buying, we apply these principles to capital allocation by letting data dictate budgets, measuring lifetime value, and requiring return on ad spend to map perfectly to business outcomes. Media buyers must exploit the delta between platform algorithm objectives and actual business needs through isolated creative testing.</p>

                                <h2>Urbanism and the East Village</h2>

                                <p>Living in the East Village is an active choice driven by an intellectual interest in urbanism. Cities function best through density, transit-oriented development, and accessible third places. Walking extensively allows me to observe micro-economies and the spatial arrangement of human lives. New York City provides a required baseline of friction that builds psychological resilience and forces continuous adaptation.</p>

                                <h2>Travel Architecture</h2>

                                <p>Travel functions as a highly technical project based on curated risk. Navigating remote four-wheel-drive tracks in Australia or undertaking intense transit routes in Latin America demands rigorous analytical preparation. Logistics rely on IATA codes and minimalist packing principles to reduce physical weight and increase cognitive bandwidth. Completing the Appalachian Trail in ninety-nine days permanently elevated my threshold for discomfort. Solo travel requires intentional design to prevent isolation. Hostels operate as a specific social technology, engineered to balance autonomy with structured social immersion. I calculate the minimum viable length for any journey to ensure experiences peak naturally.</p>

                                <h2>Flavor Mechanics</h2>

                                <p>Food represents an intersection of culture, biology, and applied thermodynamics. My research covers food science, the Maillard reaction, molecular gastronomy, and the technical precision required in high-volume kitchens. Flavor is cognitive, while taste remains genetic. Evaluating a Michelin-starred tasting menu or a local pizza slice requires the same rigorous scoring rubrics and ingredient pairing tracking. Execution and the cook's intent determine the final value on the plate.</p>

                                <h2>Philosophy of Presence</h2>

                                <p>My intellectual foundation relies on existentialism and phenomenology. The dissolution of rigid teleological frameworks forced a massive recalibration in how I construct meaning. Trying to process grief as an optimization problem fails. Human experiences are encountered organically. My governing principle is presence over optimization. Meaning accumulates incrementally through conversations, attentive meals, and paradigm-shifting texts. An honest personal inventory combats the inner critic by acknowledging both setbacks and objective achievements, such as building a career and teaching myself statistics, philosophy, and AI tooling. Tolerating uncertainty without rigidity allows for necessary emotional risk.</p>

                                <h2>Social Ecosystem</h2>

                                <p>Extroversion, hosting, and connecting form the core of my social life. I appreciate the energy of club culture and electronic dance music. Being socially skilled differs fundamentally from being truly known. I value friendships that allow vulnerability and acknowledge loneliness without demanding constant entertainment. Nourishing connections require a life that feels fully inhabited and present.</p>

                                <h2>Synthesis</h2>

                                <p>The essays on this site compress complexity into clean models using direct, specific prose. Understanding how incentives, systems, and reality function drives my analysis. This active document tracks the evolution of my thoughts on marketing incrementality, psychological resilience, and urban dining economics. The underlying objective remains extracting meaning from the raw data of human experience.</p>
                        </div>
                </main>
                <Footer />
        </body>
</html>
